The paper deals with information theoretic capacity of ad hoc networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of distributed MIMO communication, which is a topic in networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The hierarchical and digital architecture for nodal exchange of information is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the scaling laws of the network, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical theory (cs.ST). Finally, the paper discusses the cooperation between nodes, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
